    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New At Quad Kiting -- 35 Wizard's Questions</span><hr size=1> As an agnostic gnome wizard, Spankda is not KOS at the Outpost at The Overthere.  In fact, after 40 Sarnak Berzerker whips, he's now Indifferent.  Soon, he'll be Amiable and will finally be able to get that stupid hammer that proc's Gate to The Overthere Outpost.<br>
<br>
So, I've started attempting quad-kiting in The Overthere with Spankda.  The nice thing about kiting here is I can run to mommy and daddy Dragoons if things go wrong.<br>
<br>
I've successfully dual-kited a few times using my TBoots, Staff of Temp Flux, BoF, and CoF.  However, I'm not able to triple or quad-kite.  Typically because at least one MoB resists my BoF.  <br>
<br>
At that point, I've tried various strategies but nothing seems to work well.  Once, I left three snared Succulants while getting distance on the fourth.  When I finally snared the fourth after multiple resists, the three snared Succulants were gone.  They wander off somehow or BoF expires while I'm gaining that distance on the unsnared fourth.  TBoots are slower than most SoWs.<br>
<br>
The typical situation is I snare three and one resists, I run ahead with the one that resisted so I can get distance for another cast (root, stun, another snare, etc.) and I've lost the original three.<br>
<br>
At this point, I'm thinking I'll just run under the Cliff Golem's legs and let him take out the non-cooperative MoB and then go back for the others.<br>
<br>
What is the best way to handle a situation where they all don't get snared?<br>
<br>
Also, I accidentally re-cast BoF on an already snared group of two last night.  The results indicated the spell took hold.  Does this reset the timer on the BoF spell?  Can I resnare and give myself a longer time?<br>
<br>
I got a great screen shot of the whole file of Dragoons attacking and killng two unsnared MoBs I brought to them while the Dragoons were on-the-march out.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stiffu>Stiffu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/01 3:40:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hope this helps.</span><hr size=1> Quad kiting is surprisingly simple, the key to being a successful Quad Kiter is the mobs you are quading.  I'll attempt to answer some of your questions in the following. ;-)<br>
<br>
&quot;Typically because at least one MoB resists my BoF...What is the best way to handle a situation where they all don't get snared?&quot;<br>
In most Kunark zones if you run too far away from a mob then they'll stop chasing you but still remember you.  The best way to round up mobs for a quad kite is to aggro them all (with TFlux) run in a circle to bunch them all up, then run away (using Tflux to gauge distance, until you get a few out of range messages)  then stop for a second, and spam bonds of force, Dont worry even mobs with SoW won't get close enough to you during the casting time to make you snare yourself also, just make sure you are &quot;out of range&quot; before casting BoF.<br>
<br>
If you get partial resists it's ok, just take off again (I recommend circling around and running back the way you came so your snared mobs are relatively close)  Wait until out of range, and snare the mobs that resisted.  If you did this correctly you should be about to circle back around and pick up your previously snared mobs.  Get them bunched back together (you have time for 2 or 3 CoF's depending on how long you take to get them rebunched before you have to refresh BoF. . .)<br>
<br>
&quot;Can I resnare and give myself a longer time?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes.  I find that if I refresh BoF after about 8 CoF's i have ample time to get them all resnared before original snare breaks.<br>
<br>
Also, in closing, I suggest you head to Eastern wastes instead of OT to start quading.  (if you zone in from IC just follow the shore to the left until you hit a wall, you'll be in . . . SouthWest corner if im not mistaken, in this area you'll find tons of walruses, you can quad these up and down the shoreline until 38ish when you should do Ulthork Hunters and Warriors and Coldain camps (if you want to be ally in Kael)  Save all Ulthork Tusks and Coldain Heads as they are used for good quests. you can get to 43 (maybe 44 don't remember) easily.<br>
<br>
Hope it helped ;-) good luck<br>
<br>
Stiffu Noob<br>
Luclin - currently 49 wizard<br>
