<br>
I've found Tigers and Rhino's in OT to be too fast for me to kite even in singles.<br>
<br>
I'm gonna stay in OT until I get that stupid hammer with an amiable faction.  It takes 40 whips to go up one faction level (apprehensive to indifferent). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/01 2:22:32 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New At Quad Kiting -- 35 Wizard's Questions</span><hr size=1> yes, walruses, ulthraks, and coldain are all pretty slow, though I'd stay away from the coldain if I were you unless you want to join the giant faction. I highly recommend you try the drakkel wolves in greater Divide, they're pretty slow, all over the place, and have low resists to magic.<br>
<br>
As a side note, I have to say that quad kiting in GD is some of the most fun I've had with my wizard, every pull is different. sure, occasionally everything goes perfectly, snare sticks on all four,and I'm done with 40m, but more often than not 1 will resist, or something will go wrong.. and then the *Real* fun begins. there's nothing quite like having 2 dogs after you, snare about to break, and half a bubble left... 'cause then you have to make the tough calls.. re snare them and kite&amp;med until you can CoF them again? run ahead and cast harvest, hope that snare doesn't break while you're stunned? nuke one so that the other one starts to run and you have time to med to finish him off? And then what if one of *those* tactics fail, like you try to resnare, and one resists? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I can't tell ya how many times over the past 4 levels I've stood over 4 dead wolves utterly out of mana but vicorious, having been sure just seconds ago that I would never be able to pull it off.<br>
<br>
